  Fraps is a universal Windows application that can be used with games using
  DirectX or OpenGL graphic technology. In its current form Fraps performs
  many tasks and can best be described as:
  
  Benchmarking Software - Show how many Frames Per Second (FPS) you are
  getting in a corner of your screen. Perform custom benchmarks and measure
  the frame rate between any two points. Save the statistics out to disk and
  use them for your own reviews and applications.
  
  Screen Capture Software - Take a screenshot with the press of a key!
  There&#039;s no need to paste into a paint program every time you want a new
  shot. Your screen captures are automatically named and timestamped.
  
  Realtime Video Capture Software - Have you ever wanted to record video
  while playing your favourite game? Come join the Machinima revolution!
  Throw away the VCR, forget about using a DV cam, game recording has never
  been this easy! Fraps can capture audio and video up to 2560x1600 with
  custom frame rates from 10 to 100 frames per second!
